title: Make Her Want You Texting Secrets - Part 1 (Episode 189)
description:
Show Notes:

In this episode you'll get special inside access to our "Texting Guide" and real life examples of how to apply the concepts and theories to optimize your dating funnel... to purchase the product, visit innerconfidence.com/texting

The best opening texts to start a conversation... [02:00]
What if you’re getting nothing from using some of these opening lines? [04:10]
How to correctly gauge her interest by analyzing her replies... [07:33]
How to maintain the conversation and flirt to optimize your chances for a date... [10:00]
Why women are so attracted to humor... [13:00]
When and how to ask her out... [15:27]
A hilarious way to ask her out via meme... [16:57]
When should you implement the tactic of "icing?" [22:46]
What should you text leading up to the date? [37:52]
How to confirm the date... [39:05]
What if you have to reschedule? [41:47]
A weird example where a client thought he was ghosted but in reality it was something totally different and shocking... [51:50]

Links:
Get a copy of this texting guide - innerconfidence.com/texting

I'm Robbie Kramer 🎙Host of The Inner Confidence Podcast & Founder of Inner Confidence, Inc.

I lived an exhilarating single life filled with adventures and lessons, and ultimately achieved what I had always aspired to – finding an amazing, feminine, and loving wife. 

I believe my experiences provide a rare balance of wild freedom and committed love, equipping me with the insights to help you navigate the complexities of dating and relationships in today's world. Let me guide you to embrace your desires, improve your social prowess, and ultimately attract the partner who aligns with your highest aspirations.

You won’t find any fluffy, new-age, or cringy stuff here, just tested, proven and actionable advice that yields results.

Apply to join our exclusive Inner Confidence Community of ambitious men who are actively working together to achieve their goals faster   ► https://innerconfidence.com/community

You can email me at robbie@innerconfidence.com with any questions or comments.
